    "comment": "Rationale: This paper describes that \"exogenous FILIP localised to dendritic spines and dendrites of primary cultured hippocampal neurons.\"\n\n12/6/2017 Pim\nInference of actin cytoskeleton term: \"1) FILIP1 has been identified as an interactor of the actin-crosslinking protein Filamin A, see Fig 3 in PMID 12055638. In COS7 cells GFP-tagged FILIP1 shows a fibre-like distribution and co-localizes with phalloidin staining of filamentous actin (Fig 2 in PMID 12055638). Deletion of the Filamin-interaction portion of FILIP disrupts this distribution, indicating that FILIP1 can interact with the actin cytoskeleton via Filamin A. Given the similar distribution of FILIP1 and Filamin A in neurons, both enriched in spines, it is highly likely that also in neuronal spines, FILIP1 is bound to actin through Filamin A.\". Experimental description: Localization is based on overexpression of Flag-tagged FILIP. In the M&M the following is described: \"The full-length rat l-FILIP cDNA was amplified using PCR and inserted into the pCAGGS vector\". But note that the construct is expressed mouse hippocampal neurons.",
